<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Your Blog Post Title</title>

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./css/style.css">

    <!-- MathJax for mathematical formulas -->
    <script src="https://polyfill.io/v3/polyfill.min.js?features=es6"></script>
    <script id="MathJax-script" async src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mathjax@3/es5/tex-mml-chtml.js"></script>
    <script>
        MathJax = {
            tex: {
                inlineMath: [['$', '$'], ['\\(', '\\)']],
                displayMath: [['$$', '$$'], ['\\[', '\\]']]
            },
            startup: {
                ready: function () {
                    MathJax.startup.defaultReady();
                    // Add copy buttons after MathJax is ready
                    setTimeout(addMathCopyButtons, 100);
                }
            }
        };
    </script>

    <!-- Prism.js for syntax highlighting -->
    <link href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.29.0/themes/prism.min.css" rel="stylesheet" />
    <link href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.29.0/plugins/line-numbers/prism-line-numbers.min.css" rel="stylesheet" />

</head>
<body>
    <script src="./js/utils.js"></script>
    <!-- Prism.js Scripts -->
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.29.0/components/prism-core.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.29.0/plugins/autoloader/prism-autoloader.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.29.0/plugins/line-numbers/prism-line-numbers.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.29.0/plugins/toolbar/prism-toolbar.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.29.0/plugins/copy-to-clipboard/prism-copy-to-clipboard.min.js"></script>

    <div class="container">
        <header class="header">
            <h1 class="title">Your Blog Post Title Here</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">A compelling subtitle that summarizes your post</p>
            <div class="meta">
                <span class="author">By Your Name</span>
                <span>•</span>
                <span class="date">January 15, 2024</span>
                <span>•</span>
                <span>5 min read</span>
            </div>
        </header>

        <article class="content">
            <p>This is your opening paragraph. Start with something engaging that draws the reader in. You can write naturally and include <strong>bold text</strong> and <em>italic text</em> for emphasis.</p>

            <h2>Section with Math Formulas</h2>
            <p>You can include inline math like this: The famous equation $E = mc^2$ changed our understanding of physics. Or you can display block equations with copy functionality:</p>

            <div class="math-block">
                <button class="math-copy-btn" onclick="copyMathToClipboard(this)">Copy LaTeX</button>
                <div class="math-content">
                    $${{ formulas.formula1 }}$$
                </div>
                <div class="math-latex-source" style="display: none;" data-latex="{{ formulas.formula1 }}"></div>
            </div>

            <p>More complex formulas work too - hover over them to see the copy button:</p>
            <div class="math-block">
                <button class="math-copy-btn" onclick="copyMathToClipboard(this)">Copy LaTeX</button>
                <div class="math-content">
                    $${{ formulas.formula2 }}$$
                </div>
                <div class="math-latex-source" style="display: none;" data-latex="{{ formulas.formula2 }}"></div>
            </div>

            <p>Here's a matrix equation with proper LaTeX formatting:</p>
            <div class="math-block">
                <button class="math-copy-btn" onclick="copyMathToClipboard(this)">Copy LaTeX</button>
                <div class="math-content">
                    $${{ formulas.formula3 }}$$
                </div>
                <div class="math-latex-source" style="display: none;" data-latex="{{ formulas.formula3 }}"></div>
            </div>

            <h2>Including Images</h2>
            <p>Images are easy to include and will be responsive:</p>

            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/600x300/4a90e2/ffffff?text=Your+Image+Here" alt="Description of your image">
                <div class="image-caption">Caption describing what this image shows</div>
            </div>

            <h3>Code Examples with Syntax Highlighting</h3>
            <p>You can include inline code like <code>print("Hello World")</code> or beautifully highlighted code blocks:</p>

            <div class="code-block">
                <div class="code-header">Python</div>
                <pre class="line-numbers"><code class="language-python">def fibonacci(n):
        """Calculate the nth Fibonacci number using recursion."""
        if n <= 1:
            return n
        return fibonacci(n-1) + fibonacci(n-2)

    # Example usage with list comprehension
    fib_sequence = [fibonacci(i) for i in range(10)]
    print(f"First 10 Fibonacci numbers: {fib_sequence}")

    # More efficient iterative approach
    def fibonacci_iterative(n):
        a, b = 0, 1
        for _ in range(n):
            a, b = b, a + b
        return a</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h2>Advanced Mathematical Examples</h2>
            <p>Here are some more complex mathematical formulas you can copy:</p>

            <div class="math-block">
                <button class="math-copy-btn" onclick="copyMathToClipboard(this)">Copy LaTeX</button>
                <div class="math-content">
                    $${{ formulas.formula4 }}$$
                </div>
                <div class="math-latex-source" style="display: none;" data-latex="{{ formulas.formula4 }}"></div>
            </div>

            <p>Statistical formulas with summations:</p>
            <div class="math-block">
                <button class="math-copy-btn" onclick="copyMathToClipboard(this)">Copy LaTeX</button>
                <div class="math-content">
                    $${{ formulas.formula5 }}$$
                </div>
                <div class="math-latex-source" style="display: none;" data-latex="{{ formulas.formula5 }}"></div>
            </div>

            <h2>Lists and Quotes</h2>
            <p>Here's what this enhanced template now includes:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Syntax highlighting</strong> for 200+ programming languages</li>
                <li><strong>Line numbers</strong> for better code reference</li>
                <li><strong>Math formula copying</strong> - hover over formulas to copy LaTeX</li>
                <li><strong>Copy-to-clipboard functionality</strong> for both code and math</li>
                <li><strong>GitHub-inspired color scheme</strong> for familiar look</li>
                <li><strong>Responsive design</strong> that works on mobile</li>
            </ul>

            <blockquote>
                "Mathematics is the language with which God has written the universe." – Galileo Galilei
            </blockquote>

            <h2>Conclusion</h2>
            <p>This enhanced template now provides both code syntax highlighting and LaTeX formula copying functionality. Readers can easily copy mathematical expressions for use in their own documents, papers, or LaTeX editors.</p>

            <p>The copy functionality works seamlessly - just hover over any block equation and click the "Copy LaTeX" button. Perfect for academic blogs, mathematical tutorials, and scientific documentation!</p>
        </article>

        <!-- Social Sharing Section -->
        <div class="social-sharing">
            <div class="share-buttons">
                <a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u={{ request.url if request else '' }}" class="share-btn facebook" onclick="shareOnFacebook(); return false;" title="Share on Facebook">
                    <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
                        <path d="M24 12.073c0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12s-12 5.373-12 12c0 5.99 4.388 10.954 10.125 11.854v-8.385H7.078v-3.47h3.047V9.43c0-3.007 1.792-4.669 4.533-4.669 1.312 0 2.686.235 2.686.235v2.953H15.83c-1.491 0-1.956.925-1.956 1.874v2.25h3.328l-.532 3.47h-2.796v8.385C19.612 23.027 24 18.062 24 12.073z"/>
                    </svg>
                    Facebook
                </a>

                <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url={{ request.url if request else '' }}" class="share-btn linkedin" onclick="shareOnLinkedIn(); return false;" title="Share on LinkedIn">
                    <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
                        <path d="M20.447 20.452h-3.554v-5.569c0-1.328-.027-3.037-1.852-3.037-1.853 0-2.136 1.445-2.136 2.939v5.667H9.351V9h3.414v1.561h.046c.477-.9 1.637-1.85 3.37-1.85 3.601 0 4.267 2.37 4.267 5.455v6.286zM5.337 7.433c-1.144 0-2.063-.926-2.063-2.065 0-1.138.92-2.063 2.063-2.063 1.14 0 2.064.925 2.064 2.063 0 1.139-.925 2.065-2.064 2.065zm1.782 13.019H3.555V9h3.564v11.452zM22.225 0H1.771C.792 0 0 .774 0 1.729v20.542C0 23.227.792 24 1.771 24h20.451C23.2 24 24 23.227 24 22.271V1.729C24 .774 23.2 0 22.222 0h.003z"/>
                    </svg>
                    LinkedIn
                </a>

                <a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url={{ request.url if request else '' }}&text={{ 'LLM Math Reasoning Evaluation' | urlencode }}" class="share-btn twitter" onclick="shareOnTwitter(); return false;" title="Share on X (Twitter)">
                    <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
                        <path d="M18.244 2.25h3.308l-7.227 8.26 8.502 11.24H16.17l-5.214-6.817L4.99 21.75H1.68l7.73-8.835L1.254 2.25H8.08l4.713 6.231zm-1.161 17.52h1.833L7.084 4.126H5.117z"/>
                    </svg>
                    X (Twitter)
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Toast notification element -->
    <div id="copyToast" class="copy-toast"></div>

    <script>
        // Social sharing functions
        function shareOnFacebook() {
            const url = encodeURIComponent(window.location.href);
            window.open(`https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=${url}`, '_blank', 'width=600,height=400');
        }

        function shareOnLinkedIn() {
            const url = encodeURIComponent(window.location.href);
            window.open(`https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=${url}`, '_blank', 'width=600,height=400');
        }

        function shareOnTwitter() {
            const url = encodeURIComponent(window.location.href);
            const text = encodeURIComponent(document.title);
            window.open(`https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=${url}&text=${text}`, '_blank', 'width=600,height=400');
        }
    </script>

</body>
</html>